= How to run

== Environment Variable
* Set environment variable "SCALE_SYS" depending on your environment
* Makedef.${SCALE_SYS} file in the scale3/src/sysdep directory is used in compiling
* You might need to modify the Makedef.${SCALE_SYS} file.
* example
 % export SCALE_SYS=Linux64-ifort

== compile
 % cd scale3/src
 % make
* Compiled execution files are installed to the scale3/bin/${SCALE_SYS} directory

== run
* You can generate input data by your self, or download it from http://***/* for some cases.
* If you download the input data, skip the process of generation of input data file.
=== generate input data file
==== initial data
 % cd scale3/run
 % ../bin/${SCALE_SYS}/scale3_init_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_ ./scale3_init_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_.cnf
* input data
  No
* output data
  * initial data: init_turbulence_63072000000.000.pe000000.nc
  * log file: LOG.pe000000
* spinup
 % ../bin/${SCALE_SYS}/scale3_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_ ./scale3_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_spinup.cnf
* input data
  * initial data: init_turbulence_63072000000.000.pe000000.nc
* output data
  * restart data: restart_00000003600.000.pe000000.nc
  * boundary data: boundary.pe000000.nc
  * log file: LOG.pe000000

=== benchmark run
 % ../bin/${SCALE_SYS}/scale3_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_ ./scale3_1256x8x8_kessler_real8_.cnf
* input data
  * initial data: restart_00000003600.000.pe000000.nc
* output data
  * history data: history.pe000000.nc
  * boundary data: boundary.pe000000.nc
  * log file: LOG.pe000000
